PharmML.ct:Name: Glucose kinetics in humans: a unique model for different tests
PharmML.ct:Description: This is a model for glucose kinetics in humans, including a physiology-based mechanism for glucose uptake saturation. It is able to describe the relationship between glucose utilization and glucose and insulin concentrations during different tests, such as the clamp, the oral glucose tolerance test and the mixed-meal test. By Roberto Bizzotto, Institute of Neuroscience, CNR, Padua, Italy. Copyright 2016
